The electric field strength \(E\) between two parallel plates is given by \(E = \frac{V}{d}\), where \(V\) is the potential difference across the plates and \(d\) is their separation. To reduce \(E\):  
1. **Reduce the potential difference (p.d.) across the plates**, as \(E\) is directly proportional to \(V\).  
2. **Increase the separation of the plates**, as \(E\) is inversely proportional to \(d\).  

\boxed{1.\ \text{reduce}\ \text{p.d.}\ \text{across}\ \text{plates}}  
\boxed{2.\ \text{increase}\ \text{separation}\ \text{of}\ \text{plates}}
